"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    The theoretical therapeutic and toxic effect curves of antihypertensive agents vary based upon the administered dose. The theoretical effects of a single drug given at two different doses (10 and 20 units) are shown. At a dose of 10 units, the antihypertensive agent has a minimal toxic effect (A') and a moderate therapeutic effect (A). Doubling the dose, however, is associated with substantial toxic effects (B') but little increase in therapeutic efficacy (B).",
